```{r}
# Synthetic biology market data
market_data <- data.frame(
  Year = c(2018, 2019, 2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025),
  Market_Size_Billion = c(8.9, 10.8, 13.1, 15.8, 19.1, 23.1, 27.9, 33.7),
  Investment_Billion = c(2.1, 3.8, 7.8, 15.2, 11.9, 8.4, 10.2, 12.5)
)

p1 <- ggplot(market_data, aes(x = Year)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Market_Size_Billion, color = "Market Size"), size = 1.2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Investment_Billion, color = "Investment"), size = 1.2) +
  labs(title = "Synthetic Biology Market Growth and Investment",
       x = "Year", y = "Billion USD", color = "Metric") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Market Size" = "#2E86AB", "Investment" = "#A23B72"))

ggplotly(p1)

```

## Regulatory Landscape

::::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}
**United States:**

-   FDA oversight for medical applications
-   EPA regulation for environmental releases USDA for agricultural
    products
-   NIH guidelines for research
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}
**European Union:**

-   Novel Food Regulation
-   Deliberate Release Directive
-   Clinical Trials Regulation
-   REACH for chemicals
:::
:::::

AI-generated regulatory landscape overview

## Ethical Considerations

::: incremental
-   Dual-use research: Potential for beneficial and harmful applications
-   Environmental impact: Unintended ecological consequences
-   Equity and access: Fair distribution of benefits
-   Informed consent: Public understanding and acceptance
-   Governance: Appropriate oversight and regulation
:::

Source: Nature Biotechnology Ethics Review (2021)

## Technical Challenges

::::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}
**Current Limitations:**

-   Unpredictable biological behavior
-   Context-dependent part performance
-   Limited standardization
-   Scaling manufacturing processes
-   Computational design tools
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}
**Research Directions:**

-   Machine learning integration
-   Improved predictive models
-   Advanced characterization methods
-   Automated design-build-test cycles
-   Standardized measurement protocols
:::
