## Future Directions: Synthetic Biology 2.0

::: incremental
-   Artificial intelligence integration: ML-guided design and
    optimization
-   Automated laboratories: Robotic design-build-test cycles
-   Minimal cell platforms: Simplified chassis organisms
-   Orthogonal biological systems: Isolated genetic codes
-   Tissue and organ engineering: Complex multicellular systems
:::

AI-generated future synthetic biology landscape

